The party's KwaZulu-Natal leadership is meeting this weekend to discuss a report into the allegations against Zandile Gumede. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - eThekwini mayor Zandile Gumede may learn her fate as early as next week. The ANC Provincial Executive Committee (PEC) of KwaZulu-Natal will meet this weekend to discuss, amongst other things, a report into allegations against her. EXCLUSIVE: eThekwini mayor breaks her silence Gumede is currently out on bail, facing fraud and corruption charges. She’s been on special leave since June following pressure from opposition parties. WATCH: Police fire stun grenades to disperse Zandile Gumede supporters “We believe the team has finalised to a certain extent their report,” said ANC provincial spokesperson Nomagugu Simelane-Zulu. “If PWC is happy with the report, it will have to go to the PEC. We believe those might be finalised in the upcoming PEC on Sunday and Monday,” she said.